Problem Description - Write an SQL query to report the first name, last name, city, and state of each person in the Person table. If the address of a PersonId is not present in the Address table, report null instead.

Return the result table in any order.


My Answer: 
SELECT Person.FirstName, Person.LastName, Address.City, Address.State
FROM Person
LEFT OUTER JOIN Address ON Person.PersonID = Address.PersonID


